        "type": "text",
        "text": "TL;DR We tackle the problem of synthesizing images at arbitrarily sizes, up to infinitely large. ",
        "bbox": [
            26,
            145,
            501,
            171
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Synthesizing infinite-pixel images from finite-sized training data. ",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            25,
            201,
            298,
            223
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "A $1 0 2 4 \\times 2 0 4 8$ image composedof242 patches,independently synthesized by InfinityGAN with spatial fusion of two styles.The generatoris trained on101x101patches (e.g.,marked intop-left)sampledfrom197×197realimages.Note that training and inference (of any size) are performed ona single GTX TITAN X GPU. ",
